content:
Required editions and user permissions:
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

User permissions needed:
To remove users from a call center: Manage Call Centers

Remove a user from a call center:

1. From Setup, enter Call Centers in the Quick Find box.
2. Select Call Centers.
3. Click the name of the call center to remove the user from.
4. In the Call Center Users related list, click Manage Call Center Users.
5. Click Remove next to the user's name.

Alternatively, select multiple users and click Remove Users on the User Edit page.
title: Remove User from Call Center
